We need to establish a platform to mop up the cash generated on the streets and create an exchange system that does not depend on the conventional banking system to operate. Only then can payments succeed outside the banking system

I know some mobile money platforms here in Nigeria that bank account to wallet deposits still takes like T+2 to reflect and that is after calling the MoMo operator. Again banking system bottleneck coming to play here.

Exactly! I was going to point this out too. Moving of money from bank accounts to wallets is going to be subject to banking system being at their best behavior in this part of our world assuming the wallet holder is looking to a payment mode of convenience to achieve this.

Have you asked why most people in Kenya move their money from banks to their MPesa wallets? Friction. Mpesa is optimized for payments, banks are not. Being mobile also gives a degree of non-repudiation. Payments is about trust and non-repudiation.

Bank to bank transfers is banking". The two banks will still have their issues with positions. It also depends on the route. As for payments on the other hand, I think there are more elegant ways to solve payments solutions without the burden and bottlenecks of banking platforms"

It will depend on the transaction type. For a ticket, you can't dispute it after you have flown and many systems capture your ID in the process. You can't deny that you paid for DSTV if the decoder is in your name.

I get you but what happens if the customer disputes the hold after merchant delivers service? I just transferred from @ZenithBank to @gtbank using @Kudidotai . Debit went through, I also got the credit alert but can't access the cash We need to do something to break this.

Bankers complicate payments because they have a different motivation. The merchant wants to sell, the buyer wants to buy. The fewer the tollgates there are the better. Not all payments need to go through core banking systems immediately. You could have holds.

There is something we are working on. The most important thing to the billers is that you can pay and you are willing to part with the money. Settling does NOT need to happen instantly. It is already working elsewhere for small payments. Ticketing is a prime target for it.

It's a very serious issue... all our major payment channels are tied to the banking system. Except those that generate income from the street are isolated. We must all draw funds from a bank account to use alternate channels.

CBAs shouldn’t normally send OTPs. They should make available the phone no linked to the payment instrument( acct or card ), a notification abstraction layer should do that. Then payment processors can choose the channel to deliver the OTP. Can be a Twitter DM etc
I am even looking at it from a transaction point of view and not a feature POV. The original intent was to pay.
Very true but what if the CBA did not get the request to trigger the generation of an OTP?

That is why you have payment companies. Payments is NOT banking. This was a payments problem. Osarumen just wanted to buy a ticket. This is why I get very upset when they think making people banked will solve payments. People just want to transact NOT bank.
Typically sms is push. There is always the risk of it not getting delivered. Ussd is pull. OTP delivery Risk is minimized with OTP on USSD.
If the problem is with the core banking application, then the use of USSD won't make any difference.
*U.S.S.D# It is going to be everywhere. cc: @TechProd_Arch @iaboyeji
